< Text>
Since day one Packard Dental has been nothing but wonderful, professional, & welcoming. We have been coming for years and have never had a bad experience. They have recently moved into a beautiful new office that has ocean views and have the latest dental technology so they can give the best possible care to their patients. They even have blankets to give you while you get a cleaning or have other dental work done. <review>Love this dental office!  First off, I have the best hygienist I've ever had, I love you Kendra!!  I was never the type to enjoy going to the Dentist, even just for cleanings.   I hate the picking and the scraping, but Kendra makes me as comfortable as possible and is awesome to talk to throughout the process.  I have one tooth in particular, with a receding gum (caused by clenching at night) that is super sensitive and she always makes sure to numb it (topically) and is extra gentle while cleaning it.  It really makes all the difference, because I no longer dread my cleanings.

Then there is Dr. Jared.  He is seriously the friendliest Dentist I've ever met.  I can't say I'll ever understand it, but I am sure glad he loves teeth and smiles as much as he does!  He has a true passion not only for improving your smile and dental health, but also a genuine concern and passion for his patients.  Last year, he did some major work on one of my teeth...a really awkward shaped partial crown, which he had to make twice before he got it perfect (I think he's a bit of a perfectionist!) I was still having pain a few days afterwards and was concerned about it possibly being infected or something. He not only squeezed me in that day to check on everything, he also gave me his personal cell phone number in case it didn't improve over the weekend .  By the way, the work was perfect and there was no infection, just needed a few extra days for the nerves to heal. It feels good to know he and the ladies are always willing to take/make extra time for you when necessary, and I've never felt rushed during any of my appointments.  No matter how many questions you have or how many times he has to come back in and out of the room, he will make the time for you.   And somehow, they always manage to run on time for appointments...can't beat that!

In addition, the office staff has offered for me to bring my toddler in with me during my cleanings so that she can watch and get comfortable with the what goes on at the Dentist's office since she will soon be a patient of his as well.  I'm also going to be having our second baby come fall, which happens to be right at the time my next cleaning is due.  Since I will be a nursing Mom, I was concerned about whether or not I could bring the baby with me during my appointment.  Luckily the office is super family friendly and accommodating.  I know all the ladies will be willing to hold the baby if need be, and I'm happy to say I would be perfectly comfortable with that, because everyone there is great! HIGHLY RECOMMEND! <user>100106514138680337081</user><username>Amera Strong< /username>< Review>
From the moment I walked into their office, I felt welcome. I was greeted and Jill, who I spoke with initially, remembered speaking to me and even though she was on the phone when we first walked in, she said hi when she was finished with her phone call. Great first impression!

We were promptly walked back to our room where Melanie took Jaces X-Rays. This was his first time at the dentist and she did a great job helping him feel at ease.

Dr. Jared was also very friendly and came and said hello while we were waiting for Dr. Matt.

When Dr. Matt arrived to our room, he explained everything step by step and tried to make Jace feel as comfortable as possible through his exam.

Once he was near the end of his exam, he started feeling anxious but got through it, and when he completed his exam, Melanie walked him back to give him a toy, sticker, and sugar free lili-pop, he just loved it!

Very great experience I will always highly recommend Packard family dental.< /Review>

<Text>When I needed my wisdom teeth removed STAT and did not have a dentist (no seen one in years), Packard Dental took care of things immediately. They got my x-rays done as soon as I walked in the door, and were not judg-ey to the fact that I had not been seeing a dentist regularly, nor pushy to getting a ton of work done. EVERY SINGLE member of their staff were extremely friendly and accommodating. They genuinely care about their patients and worry more about their happiness and return than anything else. I even got a small bouquet after I got my teeth cleaned! Haha, it was like getting a prize for doing something one would normally dread! And your know what, it encouraged me to start setting up regular cleanings like I am supposed to- because they made what is normally a chore and something that I would put off and avoid, into a fantastic experience. <Time>1480884020245< /Time>< rate>
1<//rate>
<Review>The Holidays are rough as it is, and Ive recently had some deep personal tragic backstory type stuff happen in my world and honestly, when I finally got my appetite back I wanted comfort food. I wanted what I got as a kid, western with extra bar be que sauce, bacon, and onion rings. I wanted a chocolate milkshake and onion rings on the side.

This is a Big Deal. I havent had an appetite in a while.

The drive through speaker box wasnt working, so the heavy black man who was working that drive thru on sunday december 4th kept yelling at me to scream my order into the box. Finally i decided I didnt feel like screaming and decided to pull forward.

I have no idea how my front driver tire ended up bursting in their drive thru: he told me i was "speeding" but i never really touched the acceleration. I must have hit the curb at just the right angle, or there was something in the drive thru, because my tire popped.

This is all random and weird. The messed up part was when this same order taker peeked out the window and started making snide remarks at me.

I pulled forward into a spot and went inside. I hadnt felt like screaming into a speaker, but I definitely felt like the basic human decency that should be afforded was missing. The staff was unfriendly and cruel about my tire on my 2013 ford fusion bursting in their drive thru.

I no longer feel like eating at Carls Jr. It was a comfort food, but this location may have put me off of my appetite forever.< /Review>< Pictures>

< Text>
I really wanted to try this place since I saw their great deals for sake. Inside is really cute and clean. It is a bit small, but not crowded. We were seated immediately.

We ordered the short ribs, okonomiyaki fries, two beef bibimbap, and the chicken jjim. Of all the dishes, the chicken jjim was our favorite. The chicken and noodles were super tasty. The sauce went well with the bibimbap. I loved the fries and would highly recommend those for an appetizer. The short ribs were a great deal too. I think one downside was that there were no sides/banchan, but that's okay!

I loved this place and definitely plan to visit again soon. They have a great happy hour discount on sake. Their menu is pretty extensive and have a great selection of small plates. They're also doing take out for quarantine!<//Text>

< Text>
It's been awhile since I gave a 5 star review but this little hidden gem sure deserved it. I saw this fairly new place a week ago while running errands and stopped by for lunch with a friend today.
Since the menu classified the starters as tapas, we were going to order a few and then share a ramen or a sizzling bibimbab. The tapas were large in portions and we couldn't even finish the 4 we order. We thought we were done till they brought out the dessert menu.

Seafood Jeon $6.50
Korean savory pancake with mixed seafood
5* This was one of the best dishes, 2 small pancakes perfectly cooked. Crispy and tender at the same time.

Boneless Fried Chicken (spicy or soy garlic) $7.50
Bite size Korean style crispy boneless chicken with your choice of flavor
5* Another hit, chicken was cooked to perfection and the sauce was perfectly seasoned.

Popcorn Salmon $6
Bite size fried salmon with spicy
4* The salmon was just slightly overcooked for my liking but still divine.

Corn Cheese $6
Corn with creamy sauce and cheese on sizzling pan
3* This was average, nothing spectacular. Next time we will order the slicked beef salad instead.

I forgot to take a picture of the dessert, the Mango Panna Cotta was definetly a nice touch to end a delicious meal. I gave this restaurant 5 stars because the waitstaff was excellent. Great service with a smile!<//Text>

< Text>
My husband and I came in here after just walking around the area looking for someplace to eat. first we visited Bluefin to only find out that they open at 5 p.m. so that was a bummer, then we went to Gordo's and discovered that they only had meat for their burritos so that was a no-go. (We are pescatarian-vegan.)
Then we happen to walk across the street from Gordo's just a few feet from the stop light, and stumbled onto Jijime.

What really grabbed us was the happy hour! visit their Instagram for pics of their food!!!! Tell me to my face that food dont look good, and ill tell you, you a muhfuh lieüòÇ!!!!!!
the happy hour menu, I mean just for the sake and the beer alone I was in static shock. Then we looked at their tapas menu; It was everything we could ask for!
I mean everything we were able to have, delicious sake wine beer cocktails and small-plates that my husband and I were able to share at a very very very reasonable rate.

My husband and I are native San Franciscans! this is what we live for, in our city, to find those hidden gems and this is a city hidden Gem. If you want some happy hour eats from 3 to 6 p.m. please come here and see Hannah shout out to you Hannah because you were very sweet and you served us very well and we were very pleased, you, the cooks, and the food are the reason we are coming back!
PSA: to the vegans of San Francisco. Look no more they have a vegan and vegetarian option for their bebambib üò±. Your Welcome üòè.
Now I am going to show you below a before pic and there is no after pic because, in the words of my husband,

"WE TOOK THAT DOWN!!!"

And shout out to the cooks! They threw down! I feel so good after eating their food. The freshness! The ambiance. It was cozy and modern and quaint! Definitely will become a regular!!!!
See Ya'll Soon!!!</Text>

<Review>Stopped in after seeing a recommendation from a friend and plenty of good reviews on here. I wanted to try the katsu-don but when I asked the waitress about it she said they could not make it that evening...so I decided to order the bulgogi bowl and some okonomiyaki fries.

I didn't expect the okonomiyaki fries ($6) to be good but actually they were excellent. The fries had a McDonald's like texture but gourmet with kewpie mayo and katsu sauce finished with bonito flakes on top. Excellent.

Then the bulgogi bowl ($12.95) appeared. This bowl was a sad bulgogi bowl with disappointing small slices of meat that tasted like every Korean AYCE BBQ place I've ever been to. There was tons of green salad (with no dressing) and rice that filled the whole bowl probably at least 80% of the bowl with some clear noodles.

I would much rather pay more and have good bulgogi than pay less and have a disappointing experience. The bulgogi marinade was also super sweet, acid reflux inducing...overall just not good. I would not order it again.

The ambiance is nice here and its a good place to go with friends and maybe order some tapas, but if you really love Korean food you might find yourself disappointed at Jijime.<//Review><user_name>Carlos Hernandez</user_name><Pictures>None<//Pictures>< rate>
2< /rate>

<review>I have never seen a "soft opening" that was so smooth and excellent as Jijime's - they got everything right from the get-go:

- A varied menu, authentically Korean but fitting every possible palate
- Low prices, $5 for "Small Bites" (which are really fun), $10-14 for (big) entr√©es
- The place looks both elegant and homey, lighting, decor first-class, the music is set right, providing background, not interfering with conversations
- Service is exceptional, both genuinely friendly and responding to every need

In just a week, Jijime became a habit.

The only "however" is that this is not the kind of Korean restaurant where you get a dozen small dishes to start with. For that, go to Han Il Kwan, two blocks away from Jijime, at 19th and Balboa.</review>< Pictures>

< text>
This is probably the most tasteless, flavorless Mexican food I have had in San Diego.  The veggie burrito consisted of some dry rice, beans, tomatoes, and about a pound of lettuce.  For almost $10 with tax for a burrito, you would think they could at least cook some veggies to put inside or put some cheese or sour cream so that the burrito was not just dry and overly crunchy from so much lettuce.  They also don't offer any type of condiment bar like almost every other Mexican food place has.  They don't offer lemons, limes, various hot sauces, jalapenos, onions or spicy carrots.  So there is nothing to add any flavor to their flavorless lettuce burrito.< /text>

<pictures>None</pictures><review>They asked me for a flat fee of $35 to true one wheel, without taking a very close look. That seems very high -- I think bike shops normally quote 15~20, and 25 at the highest.

Edit: I went to another reputable bike shop and got the job done for $15. If you want to get reasonable rates, *shop around*. This place takes one look at you and your bike, sizes you up, and "gambles" i.e. tries a high quote on you because you look like you'll pay for it on the spot. This is the worst type of repair shop, whether it's an auto repair shop or a bike shop. I remember that while I was hesitating because $35 seemed high, one of the technicians suggested buying a new wheel ("Another option is to buy a new wheel, like this one here (points to a completely different type of second-hand wheel hanging from the ceiling) it's not going to be the same color, but it'll definitely be safe". < text>
I like my bike and the rest of the gear (lights, lock and helmet) that I got at Just Ride, but it was like pulling teeth to get the sales person to talk to me about the accessories while my bike was being set up by the mechanic.

The stock of large frames was very lacking for me and my partner had an even harder time trying to find a small frame during the same visit.

A couple weeks after getting said bike, my shifters stopped working. I managed to get my chain back on and get to work as a fixie. When I took the bike into a different shop closer to my office on my way home, they told me the issue was because the shifter had been installed waaaaaaay too high on the frame; after getting that addressed (and several other minor adjustments which probably would have been covered in the "free adjustments" offered by Just Ride), the bike has ridden much more smoothly.<//text>

< text>
I cannot recommend the bike fitting that Just Ride LA provides enough. Before I came to get my bike fit at JRLA, I had gone through 3 different (and very expensive) saddles and still had no relief from lower back, knee, and groin pain (even top of the line chamois' were not helping). Everything changed when Chris fitted me. His fitting was meticulous: it included a preliminary questionnaire where he asked me everything from how I would like to ride to body measurements, refitting my clips and getting new insoles for my shoes, and the best was finally getting a saddle that actually fit and felt comfortable to sit on (turns out I prefer power saddles)! In total, the fitting lasted for two hours, but now I can ride with complete comfort and no pain. I have never had a fitting as good as this. Trust me when I say this: this fitting is WORTH EVERY PENNY!</text>

<Text>I recently placed a order with Presto grill  and ordered the omlett and 3 kobideh lunch specials which are $6.99 for my co-workers. 3< /Rate>
<name>Amanda Jahanvash</name><Pics>None< /Pics><GmapID>0x80c2c633573874e9:0x4f886aa807ea0fed</GmapID>< Review>
I sure did not expect to give Presto Grill such a low rating. But I must because overall the food was not good.

The restaurant is clean and inviting. You can sit outside on the spacious patio or inside at one of the small tables. All unexpected in the middle of the Fabric District. The waitress and cooks were nice and friendly. Service was fast. Prices were good.

The koubideh was not good. The flavor of the meat and the seasonings were bad. It tasted like they had mixed liver in with the meat when it was ground. That is not necessarily bad but in this case was way too much and affected the flavor overall.

I had the Zeresk polo and boneless chicken. It was good. The zeresk were not too sweet and not too sour. The chicken was cooked perfectly. This is hard to find as many places cut the pieces uneven
And they cook unevenly on the grill. So perfect Chicken and zeresk polo.

We took a Falafel sandwich to go. How could they make it bad? I really wanted it to be good. It came with French fries which were great. The French roll was perfect for a sandwich. Onions, pickles and lettuce were very tasty but the falafel was just bad. It didn't taste good at all. I couldn't even eat it.
I was so sad because the bread had so much potential.

Should be 2.5 Stars.< /Review>

<review>Good food. The outdoor seating gives you a good view of the busy street and the ambience of the Los Angeles life. The restroom is clean with neatly placed ornaments, the smell is floral and the floor is dry.
However, even though the outdoor seating a good choice because of the view and the ambience, if you don't like to smell of cigarette smoke, better use the indoor seating. On the inside seating, you'll be treated with a background music of the piped in music (it was Richard Clayderman album that was playing as shown on their wall TV)  and the conversation of the cook, and the flickering shadow of their ceiling fan.
Four 4-seater, three 2-seater tables inside and one 4-seater, four 2-seater tables outdoor.
A good place to enjoy Persian cuisine but don't come very hungry, their service can take some time to arrive.<//review><Pictures>None< /Pictures><Resp>None</Resp><GmapID>0x80c2c633573874e9:0x4f886aa807ea0fed<//GmapID></record>

<review>The food was decent and portion size left something to be desired... my friends & I ordered according to what the owner suggested as he said they didn't have several items that are pictured on their wall. My vegetarian platter had a large salad but it was mostly the white part of the iceberg lettuce and not very many greens. Instead of falafel they tossed a chopped up veggie burger that was purchased from Costco which I also have in my freezer at home. My friends had similar salad platters one with tiny pieces of chicken sprinkled on the top & the other with one skinny kebab. The presentation was nice & we enjoyed our meals until the verbal total was announced. We were shocked to hear our total was $41.00 for our 3 dishes when most of their dishes are advised here for $6.99!!! Not at all what we expect from a hole in the wall diner style restaurant on the east side of DTLA. When we asked for separate checks & the owner didn't want to split them up... we were the only people there so it wasn't like it was an inconvenience. I was going to pay with credit card & have my friends give me cash but then he said their credit card machine wasn't activated yet as they were under new ownership as of 3 weeks ago. When we asked for a break down of the prices he explained that the chicken was an extra $3 & the sides of tahini & hummus that we didn't order were $2 each... he brought them with the platters so naturally we assumed that came with it. We never saw an actual bill & because the items on their printed menu as well as their picture menu on their wall were entirely  different he could just charge what ever he wants. I would have never sat down if I had know I was going to pay $14 for a mediocre veggie salad & soda!!  I paid $6 for a similar platter from here that had these fantastic giant falafel balls & was the reason I came back with my friends. Funny thing is the previous owner was sitting inside the whole time & when I asked if he knew the previous owner he said it was the lady inside who had come by to get some mail.  I'm all about supporting my local businesses & keeping it in the family but I don't appreciate being lied to my face & haggling over prices... we won't be coming back here again unless his mom decides to do a free falafel day!</review><Date>1479248622973<//Date>< gmap_id>

<userid>105252257300398609660<//userid><Name>Heather L. Cantu</Name><Time>1580100479241</Time><rating>3</rating>< Review>
This was the North Palm Springs, CA location. It was not bad food wise, but the rest was questionable! The restaurant itself is clean for as busy as it is. Staff is patient and kind. But the environment and outdoors of the property does not feel safe at night at all! They NEED security. Badly.  Too much traffic and the parking is not well lit at all. I kept being approached by pan handlers and worse type people and nothing is done about it! Scary. And I am a tough woman, but still kind and do not mind helping those in need if it is legit. It was especially busy with brazen drug dealers and sex traffickers/workers prevailent in the area. Those people were not good people and kept approaching everyone, outside arriving to ise any of tje facilities there, but I will spare those details. It really made me angry and I call 911 to report it before I left after my meal, I was concerned for other innocent people, especially those with small children or woman by themselves. I do recommend carrying mace or other defense if your a woman using this location at night! And be very, very wary of your surroundings and please never walk alone!! Ever. Regarding the food... I am Vegetarian for medical reasons, so their full menu does not have many items that cater to those with diet restrictions or health preferences to choose from. It was late or I would have found somewhere else that did. So I went with their sour cream and chive baked potato with extra cheese sauce on the side. It was good. The menu is a little too pricey though, for fast food in my opinion! But the food is always good when it is made correctly. Security not so good. It is connected to a Pilot gas station a Cinnabon.  Be careful y'all. At night at least. I was literally approached by a male escort), a man selling illicit drugs, and a man asking for money. To which I kindly donated my last $1 to that I had on hand. I am a good, honest person. Not trying to create drama. I am just truly concerned for the welfare of the travelers and consumers who use this Wendy's/Pilot Station rest stop. I would hate tk see anyone get hurt just because they stopped to have a nice fast food meal. I'd give 5 stars but cannot due to my experience on their joint property outdoors. I hope this helps people in the future. And I hope they hire security officers, 2 at least to manage the doors and outdoor area for safety reasons. Stay safe everyone. ‚úå‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê üôèüòá< /Review>
